Solution:
The area of $\triangle ABC$ is $\frac{1}{2} \cdot AB \cdot h,$ where $h$ is the length of the altitude to $AB.$  Let $C = (x,y).$

[asy]
unitsize(0.1 cm);

pair A, B, C;

A = (0,0);
B = (36,15);
C = (20,0);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw((20,0)--(20,8),dashed);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, NE);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$h$", (20,4), W);
[/asy]

Then the equation of line $AB$ is $y = \frac{5}{12} x,$ so the distance from $C$ to line $AB$ is
\[h = |y - \frac{5}{12} x|.\]By the Triangle Inequality, $AC + BC > AB,$ so
\[\sqrt{x^2 + y^2} + \sqrt{(x - 36)^2 + (y - 15)^2} > \sqrt{36^2 + 15^2} = 39.\]Then
\[\sqrt{x^2 + y^2} > 39 - \sqrt{(x - 36)^2 + (y - 15)^2}.\]Squaring both sides, we get
\[x^2 + y^2 > (39 - \sqrt{(x - 36)^2 + (y - 15)^2})^2.\]Expanding, we get
\[x^2 + y^2 > (x - 36)^2 + (y - 15)^2 - 78 \sqrt{(x - 36)^2 + (y - 15)^2} + 1221.\]Then $78 \sqrt{(x - 36)^2 + (y - 15)^2} > (x - 36)^2 + (y - 15)^2 + 1221 - x^2 - y^2,$ so
\[6084 (x - 36)^2 + 6084 (y - 15)^2 > (x - 36)^2 + (y - 15)^2 + 1221 - x^2 - y^2.\]This simplifies to $3645 x^2 - 1440 xy + 3645 y^2 - 71280 x - 13635 y + 466416 > 0.$

We want to minimize
\[\frac{1}{2} \cdot AB \cdot h = \frac{1}{2} \cdot \sqrt{36^2 + 15^2} \cdot |y - \frac{5}{12} x| = \frac{1}{24} \sqrt{39^2} \cdot |12y - 5x|.\]This is equivalent to minimizing $|12y - 5x|.$

Thus, we want to minimize $|12y - 5x|$ subject to $3645 x^2 - 1440 xy + 3645 y^2 - 71280 x - 13635 y + 466416 > 0.$

Note that $|12y - 5x|$ is minimized when $12y - 5x = 0,$ or $y = \frac{5}{12} x.$

Then $3645 x^2 - 1440 \cdot \frac{5}{12} x^2 + 3645 \cdot \frac{25}{144} x^2 - 71280 x - 13635 \cdot \frac{5}{12} x + 466416 > 0,$ which simplifies to $131 x^2 - 9504 x + 17496 > 0.$  This factors as $3(17x - 332)(23x - 381) > 0.$

Therefore, $x \le 18$ or $x \ge 17.$  Since $x$ is an integer, $x = 17$ or $x = 18.$

If $x = 17,$ then $y = \frac{5}{12} \cdot 17 = \frac{85}{12},$ which is not an integer.  If $x = 18,$ then $y = \frac{5}{12} \cdot 18 = \frac{15}{2} = 7.5,$ so the minimum area is $\boxed{\frac{3}{2}}.$
